  "doc_id": "5506",
  "text": "As indicated above (Sect. 3.4 and 3.5), O 3 formation in the regions where Welgegund, Botsalano, and Marikana are located can be considered VOC limited, while the highly industrialized region with high NO x emissions where Elandsfontein is located could also be considered VOC limited. Rural remote regions are generally considered to be NO x limited due to the availability of NO x and the impact of biogenic VOCs (BVOCs) [CITATION_1] . However, [CITATION_2] indicated that BVOC concentrations at a savannah grassland were at least an order of magnitude lower compared to other regions in the world. Therefore, very low BVOC concentrations, together with high anthropogenic emissions of NO x in the interior of South Africa, result in VOC-limited conditions at background sites in continental South Africa.",
